Git hooks for this repo. They are not active in a fresh clone until you
point git at this directory:

    git config core.hooksPath .githooks

pre-commit runs `src/util/autoformat --check` on the staged source files and
rejects the commit if any are not formatted (clang-format for C/C++, black for
Python), naming the files and the fix command. To bypass once -- e.g. a WIP
commit -- use `git commit --no-verify`.
